This paper deals with detecting backdoor attacks in deep neural network image classifiers, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the properties of backdoor patterns and proposes a novel detector, which involves statistical analysis, indicating the possibility of the paper belonging to the cryptography and security (cs.CR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
